  <title>&virt-scenario; scenarios</title>
  <para>
    &virt-scenario; is a tool that helps you create a &vmguest; suitable for a
    specific scenario. You can specify one of the following scenarios:
  </para>
  <variablelist>
    <varlistentry>
      <term>Secure VM</term>
      <listitem>
        <para>
          Selecting this scenario results in an encrypted and secured VM
          suitable for ...
        </para>
      </listitem>
    </varlistentry>
    <varlistentry>
      <term>Computation</term>
      <listitem>
        <para>
          This scenario puts emphasis on a high performance of the resulting
          VM.
        </para>
      </listitem>
    </varlistentry>
    <varlistentry>
      <term>Desktop</term>
      <listitem>
        <para>
          The result of this scenario is a VM suitable for running desktop
          applications.
        </para>
      </listitem>
    </varlistentry>
  </variablelist>
